parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the mechatronic unit can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to sudden loss of power, jerking, and hesitation, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden jerking or hesitation
and warning lights on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to jerk or lurch forward, making it difficult to control, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden jerking or lurching forward
and may display warning lights on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, making it difficult or impossible to accelerate, and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may experience sudden loss of power
and warning lights on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the water pump can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power steering, coolant leaks, and potentially causing accidents or stranding the driver on the side of the road.
symptoms: coolant splattered all over the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electronic parking brake can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents, damage to property, or injury to occupants or bystanders.
symptoms: The electronic parking brake disengages randomly
the vehicle rolls or moves while parked
the vehicle moves unexpectedly on a sloped surface.
